<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Which browsers does Aura support?"/>


    <p>Aura supports  the most recent stable version of the following web browsers across major platforms, with exceptions noted:</p>
       <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
          <thead>
              <tr>
                     <td><b>Browser</b></td>
                     <td><b>Notes</b></td>
              </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
              <tr>
                     <td>Chrome</td>
                     <td></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td>Safari 5+</td>
                     <td>Mac OS X and iOS</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td>Firefox</td>
                     <td></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td>Internet Explorer 9 &amp; 10</td>
                     <td>Windows only</td>
              </tr>
          </tbody>
       </table>

    <p>We recommend enabling JavaScript and cookies in your web browsers to use the full functionality of Aura. Modern browsers can take advantage of Aura's HTML5 features and older ones default to available alternatives.</p>
</aura:component>
